description.narrative:
The Women’s Empowerment team in The Hague, will develop and implement, together with country offices and partners, multi-country programs on issues related to Gender Justice and Women’s rights. Oxfam Novib has identified three main areas of work: • Women’s BodilyIntegrity, in particular Violence against Women and Girls and, Women’s Sexual and Reproductive Health Rights. • Women’s Political Participation and Transformative Leadership for Women’s Rights • Women’s Economic Empowerment.
Overall Objective: Develop and implement high quality programs and projects – with a concrete and strategic WIN-strategy.
Specific Objectives: 1. Develop program proposals through co-creations process in the areas of (1) Women’s Bodily integrity/ Sexual and Reproductive Health and Rights (SRHR)/ Violence against Women (VAW) and (2) Women’s Political Participation (WPP) 2. Participate in program development led by other thematic units and Country Offices, amongst others on Women’s Economic Development. 3. Develop fundraising strategy, including amongst others mapping of relevant donors; of other stakeholders working in these areas; and of topical subjects

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
